content: MADRID, May 5 (Reuters) - Spain's Caixabank said on Friday its net profit rose 21% in the first quarter from the same period in 2022 thanks to higher lending income.

The lender reported a net profit of 855 million euros ($944.18 million) in the January to March period compared to 706 million euros in the first quarter last year.Analysts polled by Reuters expected a net profit of 643 million euros.($1 = 0.9056 euros) (Reporting by Jesús Aguado, editing by Inti Landauro)
